A Star Point Pattern (46)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b Black to Play.\b0
\par When white invades the corner at the 3-3 point, black 2 and 4 are usually strong responses when there is a black stone around \'a1\'e3.
\par
\par White 5, seems a little strange, however, this is a standard pattern.
\par }
