Diagram 2 (Basic Pattern)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par It is normal for white to hane at 1 in exchange for black 2.
\par
\par White \'a1\'e2 is known to have been invented by Master Oh Cheong Wuon(Go Seigen/\'e7\'ef\'f4\'e8\'ea\'b9).
\par
\par \pard\ltrpar\nowidctlpar\qj After 2, white hanes at \b\f1 A\b0\f0  at an opportune moment. however, the ladder after black \b\f1 B\b0\f0 ,\b\f1  \b0\f0 white\b\f1  C\b0\f0 , black\b\f1  D\b0\f0  should be favorable for white. It is difficult to grasp but please note that there is this kind of potential in this position.
\par }
