Diagram 3 (White Plays Elsewhere)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par If white plays elsewhere in this situation, it is good for black to play a forcing move at 1.
\par
\par White cannot do much more than simply connect at 2.
\par
\par If there is no other urgent points on the board, it is a big move for black to extend to 3, making impressive thickness.
\par
\par }
